// File          : TC_003_AddPlotStepDefinitions.java
// Package       : stepdefinitions
// Description   : Step definitions for TC_003 — Add Plot dialog flow.
//                 Covers the full Add Plot form within the biss-add-plot Angular dialog:
//                   - County (searchable mat-select via lib-biss-select-search)
//                   - Townland (searchable mat-select — disabled until County is selected)
//                   - Plot Reference (text input)
//                   - Ownership Status (standard mat-select)
//                   - Organic Status (standard mat-select)
//                   - Claimed Area (number input)
//                   - Commonage Plot / Island Plot (checkboxes)
//                   - Plot Use (searchable mat-select via lib-biss-select-search)
//                   - Map Amendment Type (radio buttons)
//                   - Cancel / Next buttons
//
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//  SEARCHABLE DROPDOWN PATTERN — County, Townland, Plot Use
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//  These dropdowns use <lib-biss-select-search> + <ngx-mat-select-search>.
//  The panel contains a search <input> as the FIRST disabled mat-option.
//  Standard performMatSelect() fails because:
//    1. getText() on the search row returns empty — safe, but wastes time
//    2. The search input is not a mat-option — typing into it filters the visible options
//    3. After typing, only matching mat-options remain — click the first visible one
//
//  Correct interaction sequence for searchable dropdowns:
//    Step 1 — Click the mat-select trigger to open the panel
//    Step 2 — Wait for the panel + search input to appear
//    Step 3 — Type the search value into the search input
//    Step 4 — Wait for filtered options to appear
//    Step 5 — Click the mat-option whose text matches (excluding the disabled search row)
//    Step 6 — Wait for panel to close
//
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//  SCREENSHOT USAGE
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//  Call this single line anywhere in any step to add a screenshot to the Word report:
//    CommonFunctions.addScreenshotToReport(Hooks.iDocument, Hooks.iDocPath, Hooks.iTestCaseID);
